issue.title: Item Score
issue.body:
I think discussing on here is better instead over texts, easier to keep records and go back to.

So, item score. This is open-ended but really important to our success because it allows users to (hopefully) find items of similar interest. Let's get a list of ideas:
1) Weight vector, where each element corresponds to the how often the user rents from a certain category. For examples, if the categories are ["Mens", "Electronics", "Books"], and a user tends to be renting a lot of books, few electronics, and no mens items, his weight vector would look something like: [0.01, 2, 25]. We can experiments with either addition or multiplication for promotion after each rent event.
- weight vector will be a property of the user class
- if a user is not logged in, set all category scores to 1.0 (aka just return x closest items)
- need to find a way to factor in location (should we, at all? How about return 100 closest items from the database, then calculate scores, and finally return a list of those 100 items ordered by score? )
- what happens when we add/delete a category? We will have to update weight vectors for EVERY user in the database, which is not good. On the other hand, how often will we be making new/deleting categories?
